# ─── Cómo funciona en GitHub ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Pattern path/glob matching el último match wins (orden importa).
# 2. Pairs con "Branch protection rules" en Settings → Branches → main:
#    - "Require pull request reviews before merging" ✓
#    - "Require review from Code Owners" ✓ ← critical para Lock policy
#    - "Restrict who can push to matching branches" → solo @alefvaras
# 3. Sin branch protection enabled, CODEOWNERS es solo informational.
# 4. Sprint 2 task: enable branch protection en GitHub Settings (post este PR).
#
# ─── Lock policy semantica (ADR 003) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Durante Sprints paralelos 3+4 (Cell A preventas, Cell B marketing+finance,
# Cell H Design Ops, Cell C inventario, Cell D whatsapp):
